{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"bane-tuber-marsh","description":"# Add deterministic reachability signals to the code-review security overlay (publicly-exposed-without-auth)\n\n## Context\nFollow-up to a278. Plan-review reasons over PROSE, so it cannot do true reachability analysis; the\ndeterministic \"is this publicly exposed?\" signals belong to the **code-review** gate, which sees the\nactual `*.tf` / Dockerfile / compose / k8s / config diff. This adds the tfsec/Checkov-style detectors\nthat flag a network service exposed to untrusted networks WITHOUT authentication — the code-level\ncounterpart to a278's T10 plan-level `endpoint_access_contract`.\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/code_review/criteria_routing.json` (the `security` / `iac` / `high-critical-security`\nentries), `src/rebar/llm/code_review/detectors.py` (deterministic detectors), the code-review security\nreviewer prompt under `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/`.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. A diff opens a security-group ingress `0.0.0.0/0` (or `::/0`) to a service port, or binds a listener\n   to `0.0.0.0`/a public IP, with no authentication configured.\n2. The current code-review security overlay does not deterministically flag \"public exposure + no auth\".\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- **Expected:** a deterministic finding on a publicly-reachable service with no auth/gateway in the diff.\n- **Actual:** no such deterministic signal exists in the code-review gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The code-review security overlay detects, on the diff, a service exposed to untrusted networks:\n      SG/firewall ingress open to `0.0.0.0/0` or `::/0`; a non-loopback bind (`0.0.0.0` / `::` / public\n      IP vs `127.0.0.1`/`localhost`/unix socket); a public LB / ingress / `associate_public_ip_address=true`\n      / public API-Gateway route.\n- [ ] Pairs the exposure signal with an auth-absence check (deny-by-default): a public listener with no\n      authn config / no authenticating gateway is flagged; loopback-only / gateway-fronted /\n      private-CIDR-sourced services are not.\n- [ ] FP guards: a private-CIDR-sourced or named-SG ingress is LOWER severity, not a hard block; existing\n      boundary controls (gateway / service-mesh mTLS / network policy) that may live outside the diff are\n      considered before BLOCK. Aligns with + cites tfsec (`aws-vpc-no-public-ingress-sgr`) / Checkov SG checks.\n- [ ] Fires on the code-review file-glob triggers (`*.tf` / Dockerfile / k8s / compose), NOT on plan prose.\n- [ ] Unit tests covering a positive (0.0.0.0/0 + no auth) and a negative (loopback / private-CIDR); `make lint` green.","id":"830a-e372-3c66-4a14","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Deterministic public-exposure-without-auth detectors in the code-review security overlay (tfsec/Checkov-style)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782906729003878001,"uuid":"84bd7493-ee24-4db7-9625-fc9bcddc07c7"}